column14: you can learn more about citationsy at www.citationsy.com they have free plans and they are based in Germany so they take privacy more seriously than other sites...

Hello! I am the processor of the survey. The aim of the survey are various. 1) does subjective happiness (q1-4) vary by academic topic? tenure and other factors? 2) what disciplines are happiest? 3) is use of mendeley etc... correlated with h-index? 4) is h-index correlated with happiness?  Your responses will never be linked to you personal information. Information will only be aggregated at discipline level and country level and anonymized. No emails will be stored except for those that have indicated that they want to participate in a follow up survey in a few months.  For more questions and great suggestions (thank you) ask me on twitter @jj_berens or linkedIn :) thank you for your help
For information, my position is in France, since tenure systems are very different from one place to another...

You may ask about how much self-worth someone attributes to their work achievements or how much purpose they see in their work. I can tell that I am extremely stressed in my current job because I work full time and do a PhD on top of that. Having  paper pressure in computer science does indeed contribute to some physical health issues. On the other hand I love being a researcher and cannot imagine discontinuing my PhD. I see value in what I am doing and do not worry too much about external validation such as citations. This is why I am both, stressed but still kind of happy.
H index depends on citation index used

column14:
Well, I would like to mention few things, the most important thing I would like to mention in the survey. I hate the system. The system of sending recommendation letters during application (any postdoctoral, doctoral). This is wrong, a candidate might be very independent without having `good image' to his/her supervisor. This brings the possibility of nepotism,  abuse (both mental and physical) from the people in higher academic hierarchy. I have faced/seen such things. This is really a corrupted system. A candidate must be judged based on his/her performance, works, merit nor what his/her supervisor/someone in higher academic power say about the candidate. During postdoctoral application, I have seen that you can not even apply if you do not have a certain number of recommendation letters from people in higher academic hierarchy. 
Secondly, the international journals (the referees and editors) has to be more liberal with someone working from a third world country.

column12: Yes,  maybe in a few months
column14:
This is the important part of my response. I have been more or less mentally happy so far in my carrier, but I utterly dislike and hate the corrupted application system, this is bullshit, the system of sending recommendation letters during application (doctoral, postdoctoral etc).  This is an unfair system. This creates nepotism, physical and mental abuse to a candidate from people in higher position in academics. I have faced/seen such things in different occasions. You can not even apply if you do not have certain number of recommendation letters from people in higher academic position. A candidate can be very independent without having a `good image' to his or her supervisor. A candidate must be judged based on his works and performance not what some third person says about him/her.  This system of recommendation, nepotism must be abolished asap for the betterment of the academics.
Secondly, I have seen very good works (by researchers from third world countries) get rejected from international journals and not so good works (by researchers from first world countries) to be published easily. The international journal's editors and referees must accept equality and has to be more liberal. This is injustice.

column14:
The number of citations, in itself, does not impress me. For me, only citations by authors who are somehow inspired by my results count. While it comes to working conditions, in Poland an academic system has survived, analogous to former farms using the work of serfs (working at very low rates). For over 50 years I have been aware that the majority of native mathematical authorities operate based on availability, towards political system supervisors, and in exchange for services as we publish (we praise) your work in journals subsidized by our state, but you publish articles persons with a sufficient settlement by the domestic system.
Therefore, I have not filled in the column in which the h-index is calculated
